"v.枯萎，凋零 【英】 v.枯萎，凋零(to shrivel from loss of bodily moisture) 【考】 dehydrate : water / wither : vitality(脱水使水份降低/枯 萎使活力降低)反义词：burgeon(发 芽); revive(复活) 【记】 weather(天气)不好了 ，植物就会wither 【例】 He is withering away.(他形容日益憔 悴) v. (因失去水份而)枯萎; 凋零 【记】weather不好, 植物就会wither. 【类】dehydrate: water = wither: vitality脱水使水份降低 = 枯萎使活力降低 【反】burgeon(n /v 发芽); revive(v 复活) 【记】源自weather，风霜雪雨，随着天气变化，花会枯萎；with her 最大心愿就是与她一起变老 wither (v.)  1530s, alteration of Middle English wydderen ""dry up, shrivel"" (late 14c.), intransitive, apparently a differentiated and special use of wederen ""to expose to weather"" (see weather (v.)). Compare German verwittern ""to become weather-beaten,"" from Witter ""weather."" Transitive sense from 1550s. Related: Withered; withering; witheringly."
